# Python in this repo

## Probe / capture (current direction)

- REST: `aiohttp` to IPBox `http://<host>:30200/api/v1/...` (see knowledge doc §5).
- UDP: `scapy` or `subprocess` + `tcpdump` on macOS; capture often needs elevated privileges (`sudo`).
- Correlate each REST action with UDP payloads by monotonic timestamps; log human-readable hex + offsets.
- Sequence with ~2s gaps between actions when correlating against IPBox polling.

## REST action examples (IDs are installation-specific)

```text
GET .../action/action?id=<id>&actionType=ON&value=1
GET .../action/action?id=<id>&actionType=DIM&value=50
```

## Future central service

Keep UDP framing (field bus) separate from northbound API (WebSocket + own REST `/api/v1/` per architecture doc). Do not extend IPBox REST `:30200` parity in `gateway/rest_shim.py` — transition shim only; product API is `gateway_api.py` (not built). `gateway/rest_api.py` is a backward-compat alias to `rest_shim`.
